    Response to ConvertDialStringToE164 request that contains the converted dial strings. The response has these parameters:

    ConvertDialStringToE164Response Parameters
    switchName Always provided Specifies the name of the switch for which conversions were performed.
    resultList Always provided A list of E164ConversionResult structures of all converted E.164 numbers. The E164ConversionResult structure is described below. Note that there may be null E.164 numbers if no mapping was found.

    The E164ConversionResult structure has these parameters:

    E164ConversionResult Parameters
    resultType Always provided CONVERTED indicates that a matching rule was found and the E.164 number was successfully converted to a dial string. NO_MATCH indicates that no matching rule was found, and that the resulting dial string is null. INVALID_INPUT indicates that the given E.164 number was not a valid input string, and that the resulting dial string is null.
    e164 Usually provided Resulting E.164 number after conversion. Note that this may be null if no mapping was found.
    dialString Always provided Dial string that was converted.
